title: Sydney rally to protest Israeli PM’s visit
text:
Sydney rally to protest Israeli PM's visit Australian Associated Press February 23, 2017 9:21am 
A rally protesting against Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's visit to Australia is expected to march in Sydney. 
Speakers will address crowds at the Palestine Action Group rally, which will march from Town Hall on Thursday night. 
Mr Netanyahu's historic four-day visit has already met with opposition, as a small group of protesters held signs outside a synagogue in Bondi on Wednesday, where the prime minister gave an address. 
Palestinian academic Randa Abdel-Fattah and Greens MP David Shoebridge are among the speakers set to address the rally. 
"This rally is a response to the official Australian visit of Benjamin Netanyahu as the leader of the Israeli government, which has consistently flouted international law in relation to Palestinian rights to land justice and an end to the occupation," the organisers said in a statement.
